No, not at all.

172
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,720
I was just flustered.

173
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:56,200
Glad to hear that.

174
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,480
I'm a little curious.

175
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,401
Are investment banks really profitable?

176
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,560
You earned over a million
upon graduation.

177
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,600
Really?

178
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,641
Well...

179
00:11:09,161 --> 00:11:10,480
It depends on the situation.

180
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,200
Before the 2008 financial crisis,

181
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,401
someone could achieve it.

182
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,361
By the time I graduated,

183
00:11:16,361 --> 00:11:18,241
the crisis was abating.

184
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:19,800
It wasn't too bad.

185
00:11:21,401 --> 00:11:22,401
If I were in Google,

186
00:11:22,401 --> 00:11:23,800
I'd earn huge paychecks.

187
00:11:24,401 --> 00:11:25,761
Rather than Google,

188
00:11:25,761 --> 00:11:27,200
how about NASA?

189
00:11:28,401 --> 00:11:30,200
But we're merely foreigners there.

190
00:11:30,761 --> 00:11:31,761
We'll probably

191
00:11:31,761 --> 00:11:33,600
never have access to their core tech.

192
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,401
Do you know

193
00:11:39,401 --> 00:11:41,001
why I never urged you to stay?

194
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,521
Because I never thought

195
00:11:45,521 --> 00:11:46,641
you'd leave.

196
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,200
I thought we're two peas in a pod.

197
00:11:52,921 --> 00:11:54,401
Just like my wife said,

198
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,001
simply put,

199
00:11:56,001 --> 00:11:57,361
it was untimely.

200
00:11:59,361 --> 00:12:00,881
I also made a bet with my folks

201
00:12:00,881 --> 00:12:02,241
that if you really leave,

202
00:12:02,641 --> 00:12:03,840
I will change my name

203
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:05,881
to Pigpen Guan.

204
00:12:09,161 --> 00:12:10,521
Wouldn't that be a reunion?

205
00:12:11,241 --> 00:12:12,680
We're all siblings, right?

206
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:13,680
Shut up.

207
00:12:14,001 --> 00:12:15,401
Aren't you and I brothers?

208
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,121
Can I ask you something, Yu Tu?

209
00:12:22,521 --> 00:12:24,281
About the satellite failure,

210
00:12:24,281 --> 00:12:25,521
no one could tell what caused it.

211
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:28,480
We solved it in five days.

212
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,960
Some cases took us

213
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,761
months to solve.

214
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:34,761
If it really takes months,

215
00:12:35,241 --> 00:12:36,800
will your investment bank wait?

216
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:38,200
Or...

217
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,680
Will you run away

218
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:40,840
and abandon us?

219
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,840
